      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>>Most groups I have been in at least in higher lvls frown on someone using a pet cause it eats up the exp for the group. Everytime I have grouped w/ a mage or another necro, everyone in group says to get rid of the pet (especially in dungeons).

>I've gotten this too(with my magician), and 
>while I can see the dungeon 
>arguement(if you're wandering and not camping 
>a spot) it otherwise makes zero 
>sense. 
>I mean, "it eats up exp"?? 
>Well, sure, so does the warrior, let's 
>drop him. 
>Let's see, the pet is an expendable, 
>kicking, bashing, multi-hitting, taunting fighter that 
>regens hp faster than the mages 
>can med mana. 
>Uhuh. Oh yeah, it's healable by the 
>necro too, so the clerics won't 
>burn healing mana on it(save it 
>for the warriors). 
>Will the warrior that's 10 zones from 
>his bind spot hang around to 
>save the party from that griffon(while 
>everyone runs away)? 
>Give me good ole bony Lobken that, 
>without thought to his own personal 
>fate, will blindly throw himself into 
>death's ugly maw to save his 
>evil master. 
>
>I would be curious to know how 
>much exp pets take though. Do 
>they always take a warrior's group 
>share, or does a set amount 
>go to them(say 50%) before getting 
>split to the group? 
>If they always took a 50% chunk 
>before group splits, I'd call that 
>a bug. 
>If they only take a warrior's share, 
>then groups are crazy to not 
>have pets around. 
